","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["New Testament name, borne by one of Christ's twelve apostles, referred to as ‘Thomas, called Didymus’ (John 11:16; 20:24). <i>Didymos</i> is the Greek word for ‘twin’, and the name is the Greek form of an Aramaic byname meaning ‘twin’. The given name has always been popular throughout Christendom, in part because St Thomas's doubts have made him seem a very human character."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Thomas A Meade was born about 1362, in Gloucestershire, England, United Kingdom, his father, Thomas A Meade, was 36 and his mother, Nichole, was 34. He had at least 1 son with Agnes Wycliff."},"et":{"Abt 1362–":"umbes 1362–Surnud","1362–Male":"1362–Surnud","1360–1395":"1360–1395","1387–1455":"1387–1455","1328–1397":"1328–1397","1330–1397":"1330–1397","Abt 1362":"umbes 1362","1455":"1455","Abt 1387":"umbes 1387","1387":"1387","1397":"1397","1330":"1330","1395":"1395","1362":"1362","1360":"1360","1328":"1328","Mead's Place, Wraxal, Gloucestershire, England":"Gloucestershire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"Abt 1362–":"noin 1362–Kuollut","1362–Male":"1362–Kuollut","1360–1395":"1360–1395","1387–1455":"1387–1455","1328–1397":"1328–1397","1330–1397":"1330–1397","Abt 1362":"noin 1362","1455":"1455","Abt 1387":"noin 1387","1387":"1387","1397":"1397","1330":"1330","1395":"1395","1362":"1362","1360":"1360","1328":"1328","Mead's Place, Wraxal, Gloucestershire, England":"Gloucestershire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"Abt 1362–":"environ 1362–Décédé","1362–Male":"1362–Décédé","1360–1395":"1360–1395","1387–1455":"1387–1455","1328–1397":"1328–1397","1330–1397":"1330–1397","Abt 1362":"environ 1362","1455":"1455","Abt 1387":"environ 1387","1387":"1387","1397":"1397","1330":"1330","1395":"1395","1362":"1362","1360":"1360","1328":"1328","Mead's Place, Wraxal, Gloucestershire, England":"Gloucestershire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary